Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_virtual_fin_bound_marker(25.10)  create_virtual_fin_bound_marker(25.10)

Name
       create_virtual_fin_bound_marker

Syntax
       create_virtual_fin_bound_marker

       [-help]

       [-areas {{<lx1 ly1 ux1 uy1>} {<lx2 ly2 ux2 uy2>}...}]

       {[-cell   {<libCell   |   ptnCell>}   |   -inst   <inst_name>|  [-layer
       {<metal_layer_name>| <via_layer_name>} [-net <net_name>]]}

       [-drc_region_layer <drc_region_layer_name>]

       -marker_layer <marker_layer_name>

       Creates a Fin Bound (FB) marker to stream out signal routing wires (in-
       cluding via metal layers) or bounding box instances to the specific GDS
       layer. The routing wires or instances can be selected per the  area  or
       DRC region. If this command is used to create an FB marker on:

              * An  instance,  the cell shape will be marker, which means that
                the polygon shape will be supported.

              * A layer, the shape will be created on all the specified layers
                (including those for wires and vias). For example, if the com-
                mand is used with specifying -layer M3, it will create  an  FB
                marker  on  all  the  wires  whose  layer  is  M3, and all the
                top/bottom metal layers with name M3.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each create_virtual_fin_bound_marker parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man create_virtual_fin_bound_marker

       -areas {{<lx1 ly1 ux1 uy1>} {<lx2 ly2 ux2 uy2>}...}
              Specifies the area regions to find the marker shapes.

       -cell <libCell>
              Creates marker shapes with the specified boundary box cell.

              This parameter is exclusive to the -layer parameter.

       -drc_region_layer <drc_region_layer_name>
              Adds marker shapes on the objects, which touched  the  specified
              DRC region layer.

       -inst <inst_name>
              Creates marker shapes with the specified boundary box instance.

              This parameter is exclusive to the -layer parameter.

       -layer {<metal_layer_name>| <via_layer_name>)
              Filters marker shapes by the specified metal or via layer name.

       -marker_layer <marker_layer_name>
              Specifies the customized layer name to put the marker shapes.

       -net <net_name>
              Filters marker shapes by the specified net name.

